spans.content: EDWARDS 890 Series Lamp Stations are designed for placement
on the wall or ceiling above fire alarm manual pull stations. Wired
with the individual fire alarm station, the corridor lamp will “light up”
and visually indicate when that station has been “pulled”. This al-
lows the building authorities to quickly recognize what pull station
All models feature a large translucent plastic lens easily seen from
all angles. WHITE or RED lenses are available to meet local re-
quirements. Red lenses have “FIRE” printed in white; white lenses
EDWARDS 890 series Lamp Stations are supplied with 24 volt
(0.18 amps) or 120 volt (0.05 amps) lamps, supervision diode,
wedge shaped plastic lens and two-gang brushed stainless-steel
face plate. Wiring connections are made to six-inch (150mm) wire
These Lamp Stations flush mount over standard North American
one or two-gang electrical boxes, or surface mount to two-gang
